                        <span>**Microtubules**: The proboscis should have similarly structured Microtubule networks as human axons.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-vagus-dark pt-8 border-b border-vagus-border pb-4">Implications for Therapy</h2>
            <p>If the Vagus Nerve is indeed a "living fossil" inside us, then <a href="/ultrasound" class="text-vagus-blue font-bold hover:underline">Ultrasound Stimulation</a> becomes even more logical. We aren't just sending signals; we are communicating with an ancient, highly intelligent regulator that responds to specific acoustic frequencies.</p>

